Subject: rtl_power: reset USB endpoint before each sync read

rtl_power from both upstream librtlsdr and the rtlsdrblog fork hangs
indefinitely in libusb_bulk_transfer (do_poll, BULK_TIMEOUT is 0) on
the RTL-SDR Blog V4. Root cause: librtlsdr's sync-read contract
requires rtlsdr_reset_buffer() to prime the USB bulk endpoint. The
rtl_test.c source marks this call 'mandatory'; rtl_power forgets it
after set_sample_rate() and inside retune(). Older dongles tolerate
the missing reset because their bulk endpoint auto-primes on first
transfer; the V4's R828D does not. [MESHSAT-509]

--- a/src/rtl_power.c
+++ b/src/rtl_power.c
@@ -543,6 +543,7 @@ void retune(rtlsdr_dev_t *d, int freq)
 	rtlsdr_set_center_freq(d, (uint32_t)freq);
 	/* wait for settling and flush buffer */
 	usleep(5000);
+	rtlsdr_reset_buffer(d);
 	rtlsdr_read_sync(d, &dump, BUFFER_DUMP, &n_read);
 	if (n_read != BUFFER_DUMP) {
 		fprintf(stderr, "Error: bad retune.\n");}
@@ -962,6 +963,7 @@ int main(int argc, char **argv)
 	verbose_reset_buffer(dev);
 
 	/* actually do stuff */
 	rtlsdr_set_sample_rate(dev, (uint32_t)tunes[0].rate);
+	verbose_reset_buffer(dev);
 	sine_table(tunes[0].bin_e);
 	next_tick = time(NULL) + interval;
